          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "title": "MAD HONEY FROM NEPAL",
            "subtitle": "RAW · TRACEABLE · NEPAL ORIGIN",
            "description": "<p>Mad Honey is rare himalayan cliff honey product made by Apis laboriosa from high-cliff hives located in the deep forests of the Himalayas. The Himalayan giant honeybees (<em>Apis laboriosa</em>) make it by concentrating nectar collected from wild alpine and subalpine flowers, exclusively from over 30 species of wild rhododendrons that mountain forests here harbor.</p><p>The collection method is like no other. The indigenous Gurung communities climb the cliffs and harvest mad honey hanging in the air for hours. Harvesting occurs only twice annually. Each jar hence is the limited expression of Himalayan forests, of ancient traditions, of native Himalayan communities and of the great golden bees.</p>",
            "button_text": "",
            "button_link": "",
            "button_text_2": "",
