      "settings": {
        "heading_size": "h2",
        "section_title": "What Makes Nepal Mad Honey Different",
        "section_description": "Nepal mad honey comes from some of the highest altitudes on Earth where diverse mountain vegetation layers the Himalayan forests. Coming from such an exclusive landscape of iconic Himalayan rhododendrons, it holds natural qualities of wild honey at its purest expression. Moving to harvesting, it is unlike anywhere in the world. Native Himalayan communities developed their own climbing ways to reach hives suspended on high cliffs. They established the tradition of harvesting only twice a year prioritizing the health of the bee colonies. Naturally limited by terrain, flowering seasons, and mountain harvest cycles, every batch carries a character of its own.",
