    "basmil_image_text_PefDK4": {
      "type": "basmil-image-text",
      "blocks": {
        "content_hYAFEf": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Mad Honey Hunting Expedition",
            "subtitle": "",
            "description": "<p>Witness the world’s most dangerous and adventurous honey harvest up close.</p><p>High in the himalayan mountains, the gurung tribesmen of Nepal are master honey hunters, risking their lives collecting wild honeycomb in the foothills of the Himalayas, using nothing more than handmade rope ladders, long sticks known as tangos and bamboo baskets, they harvest the legendary\"mad honey\" from the world's largest honeybee, Apis Laboriosa. </p><p>Join us in this once in a lifetime adventure honey hunt that happens twice a year in autumn and spring which takes you deep into untouched himalayan landscapes, stay at community villages in the deep forests and himalayan cliffs that hold stories older than memory. Along the way, you will also meet the honey hunters, share meals with local families, and experience a tradition that survives only in a few parts of the world.</p>",
            "button_text": "Explore The Expedition",
            "button_link": "shopify://pages/honey-hunting-tour",
            "button_text_2": "",
            "button_link_2": ""
          }
        },
        "image_Ahie3z": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image_type": "image",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/expedition.webp",
            "image_alt": "Mad Honey tour and hunting",
            "svg": "",
            "image_width": "50%"
          }
        }
      },
